&#8220;NCIS: Los Angeles&#8221; and &#8220;Crossing Jordan&#8221; star Miguel Ferrer died Thursday at the age of 61 of throat cancer.In addition to appearing on seven seasons of NCIS, the actor&#8217;s film credits include &#8220;RoboCop,&#8221; &#8220;Iron Man 3&#8221; and he will be next seen in Showtime&#8217;s reboot of &#8220;Twin Peaks,&#8221; where he will reprise his role as FBI pathologist Albert Rosenfield.Ferrer appeared in the original TV series.The actor also lent his voice to animated projects including &#8220;Mulan,&#8221; and the &#8220;Halo 3&#8221; video game.-Relaxnews